✨ WebUI: sub-header search bar, mobile layout, SSL detection, results info ✨

Sub-header search bar (non-home pages):
- Create partial/public/subheader.tmpl: full-width search bar shown
  below the header on all non-home pages; includes advanced search
  trigger button only when Page == "search"
- Remove search form from header.tmpl (was in <nav class="header-nav">)
- Wire {{template "public/subheader" .}} into base.tmpl and public.tmpl
- base.tmpl also gets public-page body class so all pages (including
  /healthz) render consistently with the sub-header

Help page $SERVER fix:
- pages.go: populate PageData.ServerURL via s.getBaseURL(r) in handleHelp
- embed.go: add ServerURL string field to PageData struct
- help.tmpl: replace all $SERVER literals with {{.ServerURL}}; remove
  the "Replace $SERVER with..." note

Search results info bar:
- embed.go: add Engines []string field to SearchPageData struct
- server.go: populate Engines from results.Engines in renderSearchResultsWithInstant
- search.tmpl: results info now shows "47 results · 3 engines: Brave,
  Google, Bing · 1.23s" instead of bare count

SSL / reverse proxy detection (opensearch.go getBaseURL):
- Previously only checked r.TLS and X-Forwarded-Proto
- Now also detects: X-Forwarded-Protocol, X-Forwarded-Ssl: on,
  X-Scheme, RFC 7239 Forwarded: proto=https
- X-Forwarded-Host now handles comma-separated values (takes first)
- Configured BaseURL still takes priority over all detection

Mobile CSS fixes (public.css):
- .search-box: flex-wrap wrap so input is full-width row 1, buttons
  share row 2 on <481px; at 481px+ restores single-row pill layout
- .subheader* styles: full-width search bar below header, pill shape,
  touch targets min-height 44px, responsive at 768px+
- .info-row: add flex-wrap wrap + gap so long values (commit SHA,
  timestamps) wrap on narrow screens instead of squishing
- .info-row code: add word-break break-all, overflow-wrap anywhere
  for long commit hashes on /healthz mobile view
